{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Vercel AI SDK + Gemini Recommended\n      Migrate the API route to use @ai-sdk/google + streamText with typed tool definitions. Each tool (webSearch, youtubeAnalysis, generateImage, analyzeFile) is declared once — Gemini decides when to call them. The SDK handles streaming, tool invocation state, and multimodal payloads automatically.\n      \n        \n          Browser\n          → stream chat →\n          /api/chat (streamText)\n          → toolCall →\n          execute(tool)\n          → result →\n          Gemini synthesizes\n          → stream to UI\n        \n      \n      \n        ProsStreaming first-class via useChatTool invocation state built-in (show badge automatically)Multimodal files & audio handled nativelyEasiest to add new tools later\n        ConsAdds @ai-sdk/google dependencyRequires refactoring existing /api/chat route","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776816916093}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Raw Gemini Function Calling\n      Keep the existing raw fetch to Vertex AI, but add Gemini's native tools / functionDeclarations to the request body. The API route runs an orchestration loop: call Gemini → handle functionCall → execute → feed result back → repeat until final text response.\n      \n        \n          Browser\n          → POST →\n          /api/chat\n          → loop until text →\n          Vertex AI raw fetch\n          → JSON response\n        \n      \n      \n        ProsZero new dependenciesStays 100% Google ecosystem\n        ConsNo streaming — full response before UI updatesOrchestration loop is tricky to get rightMultimodal / file handling is manual","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776816947478}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Intent Routing (Separate API Routes)\n      Keep the main Gemini chat route. Add dedicated routes per tool (/api/tools/web, /api/tools/youtube, /api/tools/image). The frontend pre-classifies intent (regex + keyword matching on the message) and calls the right route, showing the tool badge before the request completes.\n      \n        \n          Browser classifies intent\n          →\n          /api/tools/[tool]\n          or\n          /api/chat\n        \n      \n      \n        ProsVery simple to reason aboutEasy to debug each tool in isolation\n        ConsClient-side intent detection is fragileMulti-tool requests (search + image) don't composeNo streaming on main chat","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776816960246}
